         <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
           <p>
           <lb n="1"/><g type="svastikaLeft"/>sopāragā negama
           <lb break="no" n="2"/>sa samikupāsaka
           <lb break="no" n="3"/>sa poḍhi deyadhama
           </p>
         </div>
          
          
          
          
         <div type="apparatus">
           
               <listApp>
                  <app loc="2">
                     <lem>samikupāsaka</lem>
                      <rdg source="bib:Gokhale1991_01">sāmikupāsaka</rdg>
                      <note>There is no ā mātra.</note>
                  </app>
               </listApp>
         </div>
          
          
          
          
          
         <div type="translation">
 	      <p n="1-3">A cistern: the meritorious gift of the lay follower <persName>Sāmika</persName>, a market councillor from <placeName>Sopāra</placeName>.
 	      </p>
         </div>
          
          
          
          
         <div type="commentary">
         <p n="1">Regarding l. 1 <foreign>sopāragā</foreign>, location names in the ablative singular are found frequently in early inscriptions at Bharhut, Sanchi, and Karle (cf. III Karl 8.1 <foreign>sopārakā</foreign>). See as well <ref target="DHARMA_INSKI0003.xml">KI0003</ref> <foreign>kalīyanā suvaṇakerasa</foreign>.
         </p> 
             
         </div>
          
          
          
          
